Title
RTL Design of Finite State Machines (FSM) and Control Units

Objective:
To understand and implement Moore FSM, Mealy FSM, Traffic Light Controller, and Sequence Detector using Verilog HDL.

Moore FSM
States: S0, S1, S2
Output depends only on state.
State sequence:
S0 → S1 → S2 → S0

Mealy FSM
Output depends on current state and input.
Output becomes HIGH when input = 1 and state = S1.

Traffic Light Controller
States:
State	Light
S0	Red
S1	Green
S2	Yellow

Sequence:
Red → Green → Yellow → Red

Sequence Detector
Pattern:
1011
Detection output becomes HIGH when pattern is detected.

Observations
FSMs transition correctly with clock edges.
Reset initializes all circuits.
Traffic light sequence follows expected order.
Sequence detector successfully detects 1011.
Simulation waveforms verified functionality.

Conclusion
Task-4 provided practical experience in FSM-based RTL design, state transitions, pattern recognition, and verification through simulation.
